com.i2group.apollo.alertretrievalservice.transport

Class AlertResults

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.alertretrievalservice.transport.AlertResults

  • public final class AlertResults
extends Object
    Contains the Alerts and Items that form the results of a request to retrieve alerts.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AlertResults

        public AlertResults(AlertRetrievalToken token,
            boolean more)
        Constructs a new AlertResults, initializing all mandatory fields.

        token - The AlertRetrievalToken that client code can use in future requests for Alerts generated by the same alert feeds.
        more - true if there are more Alerts available than this AlertResults contains; false otherwise.

    • Method Detail

      • isMore

        public boolean isMore()
        Indicates whether there are more Alerts available than this AlertResults contains, due to limits placed on the amount of data to be returned.
        Returns:
        true if there are more Alerts available than this AlertResults contains; false otherwise.

      • getToken

        public AlertRetrievalToken getToken()
        Gets the (server-generated) AlertRetrievalToken that client code can use in future requests for Alerts generated by the same alert feeds.

        By passing the token back to the server in a later call, clients can opt to exclude from future AlertResults any Alerts that have already been returned.

        Returns:
        See above.

      • getItems

        public Items getItems()
        Gets the Items referenced by the Alerts in this AlertResults.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if this AlertResults contains no Alerts.

      • getAlerts

        public Collection<Alert> getAlerts()
        Gets the Alerts that this AlertResults contains.

        The number of Alerts in the collection is constrained by the limits in place at the time of the request. If there are more Alerts available than the limits allow, then the most recent Alerts are returned. However, the order of Alerts within the collection is undefined.

        Returns:
        See above, or null if there are no Alerts to return.
